doi: 10.5281/zenodo.20651093
title: "mirl-map: A reusable documentary photo-map platform"
message: "If you use this software, please cite it as below. EDIT ME: update the URLs (and your name) when you fork."
type: software
license: MIT
authors:
  - family-names: "O'Brien"
    given-names: "Jeff"
    email: "jeffobrien@ucsb.edu"
    affiliation: "Material / Image Research Lab (MIRL), University of California, Santa Barbara"
repository-code: "https://github.com/mirl-ucsb/mirl-map"
url: "https://mirl-ucsb.github.io/mirl-map/"
abstract: >-
  A no-build static platform that pairs geolocated photographs with per-photo
  written narratives, presented as an interactive Leaflet map and a sequential
  photo essay. Generalized from the "Lifta" project. Accessible, bilingual-capable,
  and deployable on any static host.
keywords:
  - "documentary"
  - "photo map"
  - "digital humanities"
  - "archives"
  - "Leaflet"
  - "GitHub Pages"
